' @anti-pattern
' @status stable
' @instead Use IF for deterministic comparisons — no LLM needed
' @description Using THINK to evaluate a condition that the runtime can check

' Wasting tokens on something the runtime computes instantly.
' IF evaluates conditions deterministically, without calling LLM.

THINK check
  GOAL <<
  Determine whether the score exceeds 80.
  >>
  INPUT <<
  Score: $evaluation.score
  >>
  RESULT
  * exceeds: FLAG - true if score is above 80
END

WAIT
  ON ?check
END

' Correct approach:
'
' IF $evaluation.score >= 80
'   ...
' END

EXIT
